          <div class="breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a></div>                              <h2>Royal Weddings Through The Ages</h2>                                                  <div class="clear-block">
            <div id="node-77" class="node">



  
  <div class="content clear-block">
    <p>To celebrate the Royal Wedding on April 29th, Mills &amp; Boon have created a special ebook collection of seven short stories.&nbsp;There are seven couples, seven royal marriages and seven different authors.</p>
<p><img hspace="10" vspace="10" align="left" src="http://www.marynichols.co.uk/sites/default/files/Royal%20weddings%20web.jpg" width="187" height="320" />My story is called WITH VICTORIA'S BLESSING:<br />
<br />
Lady Emily Sumner, only daughter of the Earl and Countess of Lynne, has met the man of her dreams and wants to marry him, but her mother, believing Lieutenant Richard Saunders is not of sufficient rank for her daughter, forbids her to see him again. The Countess is one of Queen Victoria's Ladies of the Bedchamber and the palace is in the throes or arranging Victoria's wedding to Prince Albert; she has little time for her wayward daughter.&nbsp; Only the intervention of the Queen herself will save the day for Emily. But will she help the young couple?</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The collection is also published by Mills &amp; Boon as a paperback volume&nbsp;ISBN 978 0 263 89752 4 price &pound;6.99</p>
<p>The other six stories are:<img src="/sites/default/files/Royal%20weddings%20pback%20web.jpg" width="204" height="320" vspace="10" hspace="10" align="right" /></p>
<p>What the Duchess Wants by Terri Brisbin<br />
<em>Eleanor, Duchess of Aquitaine and Henry of Anjou (future Henry II), 1152<br />
</em>Lionheart&rsquo;s Bride by Michelle Willingham<em>King Richard and Princess Berengaria, 1191<br />
</em>Prince Charming in Disguise by Bronwyn Scott<br />
<em>Prince George and Caroline of Ansbach, 1704<br />
</em>A Princely Dilemma by Elizabeth Rolls<br />
<em>George, Prince of Wales (future Prince Regent/George IV) and Princess Caroline of Brunswick, 1795<br />
</em>The Problem with Josephine by Lucy Ashford<br />
<em>Napoleon and Archduchess Marie-Louise of Austria, 1810<br />
</em>Princess Charlotte&rsquo;s Choice by Ann Lethbridge<br />
<em>Princess Charlotte and Prince Leopold, 1816</em></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;In April 2014 the collection was reissued as digital boxed set price $4.99:<img src="/sites/default/files/Boxed%20set%20All%20covers%20web.jpg" width="224" height="320" vspace="10" hspace="10" align="right" /><img src="/sites/default/files/With%20Victoria%27s%20Blessing%20web.jpg" width="202" height="320" vspace="10" hspace="10" align="right" /></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
